Drupal Static Export: Site navigation is broken when selecting a filter option on StackOverflow page The StackOverflow filtering uses history.pushState to store your previous filter in the browser history. The link set in the browser history is not correct when used in context of the Drupal static export.

The correct implementation of how to set the previous history can be seen at line 300 in search.js:

{code}
var searchPage = $window.location.protocol + '//' + $window.location.hostname + ($window.location.port ? (':' + $window.location.port) : '') + $window.location.pathname
      history.pushState($scope.params,$scope.params.query, searchPage + '?q=' + $scope.params.query);
{code}

*Definition of Done*

* Using the filtering options on the StackOverflow page does not break the site navigation on the static site export.

